21/03/2010
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Prosecutors from the National Anti-corruption Department (DNA) filed corruption charges Friday (March 19th) against Craiova Mayor Antonie Solomon.
He was arrested on March 3rd on suspicion of forgery and accepting bribes.
Local media reported that Solomon allegedly took a 50,000 euro bribe from a local businessman in exchange for a permit to build a supermarket.
After Solomon's arrest, he was suspended from the post.
On Friday, a local court turned down his request for provisional release and remanded him in custody.
(Mediafax, Jurnalul National, Adevarul - 19/03/10)
